@Endnode
@Node "Intro" "INTRODUCTION"


        Liga is a database program for soccer leagues. It not only
        keeps track of league positions but also goal scorers, goal
        type, players in the team, yellow + red cards. Unlike other 
        programs of this type you can keep track of ALL the teams in 
        the league as well as ALL players in the league, you can even 
        transfer a player from one club to another.

@Endnode
@Node "Load" "BEFORE LOADING LIGA"

        When using this program you should occassionally back up the
        data to floppy disk, just in case something goes badly wrong
        (i.e. accidental deletition of important files or some sort
        of hard drive meltdown)


        @{i}Liga system requirements@{ui}

                @{b}Computer :@{ub}    A500
                @{b}Memory :@{ub}      1MB Ram

        @{i}for program:@{ui}

                              1MB on Hard Drive
                              Color monitor
                              Mouse

@Endnode
@Node "Install" "INSTALLATION"

        To Use Liga copy :

                Liga/    ->   Anywhere you want
                Fonts/   ->   Sys:fonts/

                assign LIGA: to <program directory>

        @{b}screen font must 8 pixel high@{ub}

        @{i}For English Localization copy@{ui}

                Liga.cd       -> Sys:Locale/
                English.ct    -> Sys:Locale/
                Liga.catalog  -> Sys:Locale/catalogs/English/

        Now you can @{"start Liga" link "Start"}

@Endnode
@Node "Start" "STARTING LIGA"

        To Load Liga follow these steps :

             1) Load Workbench
             2) Open up the Liga drawer icon
             3) Double-click on the Liga icon
             4) Wait while Liga loads
             5) When loaded open a file or @{"create a new league" link "New"}


@Endnode
@Node "New" "CREATING A NEW LEAGUE"

        When starting Liga for the first time you will have to 
        create a new league and @{"Configure" link "config1"} it to you requirements.

        To create a new league

             1) Select NEW from the Project menu
             2) Select the Number of Teams in the League
             3) Select the number of times each team play each other
             4) Edit the Team Names
             5) Select Players from Division menu
             6) Enter Players Names, Position and Date of Birth for 
                all teams
             7) Select Calander from Division menu
             8) Enter fixtures for the season
             9) Select Save As from the Project menu and enter a 
                filename.

        The League is now ready
@Endnode
@Node "Insts" "FUNCTIONS"

    Click on button to find out what the menu option does

     @{b}Project        Division        Preference          Import@{ub}

    @{" OPEN    " link "page1"}    @{" TEAM NAMES   " link "team"}    @{" GLOBAL " link "global"}    @{" FROM LIGA345        " link "import"}
    @{" SAVE    " link "page1"}    @{" CALENDER     " link "calender"}    @{" LOCAL  " link "config1"}    @{" FROM LIGAMASTER     " link "import"}
    @{" SAVE AS " link "page1"}    @{" PLAYER NAMES " link "players"}                 @{" FROM MUI LIGAMASTER " link "import"}
    @{" NEW     " link "page2"}       
    @{" ABOUT   " link "page2"}                                       @{b}Buttons@{ub}
    @{" QUIT    " link "Page2"}
                                                  @{" FIXTURE    " link "fixt"}
                                                  @{" STANDINGS  " link "stand"}
                                                  @{" SCORERS    " link "scorers"}
                                                  @{" BOOKINGS   " link "cards"}
                                                  @{" STATISTICS " link "stats"}
                                                  @{" MATCHES    " link "matches"}

@Endnode
@Node "page1" "MENU ITEMS PAGE 1"
@TOC "insts"



        @{b}Open :@{ub}    As it says this just opens the selected league file

        @{b}Save :@{ub}    This simply saves the file currently opened

        @{b}Save As :@{ub} This saves the file currently opened with a filename
                  that you have selected


@Endnode
@Node "page2" "MENU ITEMS PAGE 2"
@TOC "insts"



        @{b}New :@{ub}   This allows you to create a @{"new league" link "new"}

        @{b}About :@{ub} Information about LIGA, the Author and Thanks

        @{b}Quit :@{ub}  Obviously, quits the program. Be sure you have saved
                any changes made itherwise they will be lost.

@Endnode
@Node "team" "TEAM"
@TOC "insts"


        This option allows you to :

                Edit team name : To edit just click on the name and 
                                 type in the new text

                Sort teams : Clicking on this button will sort the 
                             teams into alphabetical order

                Save : Select this to save any changes you have made

@Endnode
@Node "players" "PLAYERS"
@TOC "insts"

        Selecting this menu item gives you the opportunity to edit
        information relating to a teams players, such as :

                        @{" ADD      " link "add"}
                        @{" TRANSFER " link "other"}
                        @{" DELETE   " link "other"}
                        @{" PAGE     " link "other"}
                        @{" SORT     " link "sort"}
                        @{" PRINT    " link "other2"}
                        @{" TEAM     " link "other2"}
                        @{" SAVE     " link "other2"}

@Endnode
@Node "add" "ADDING PLAYERS"
@TOC "players"

        @{b}Add :@{ub} This enables you to add a player to the current team.
              Once selected there are three attributes to be edited

                Players Name - Type in the players name in the left most 
                        window and press enter

                Position - This can be changed by clicking on the middle 
                        window. The positions available are Goalkeeper, 
                        Defender, Midfield or Striker

                Date of birth - Type this in the right most window in the 
                        format D.M.Y. i.e. 060873 for 6th August 1973

@Endnode
@Node "sort" "SORTING PLAYER INFORMATION"
@TOC "players"

        This allows you to select how the players are sorted. The
        options available are:

                Sort by First name
                Sort by Last name
                Sort by position down - GK -> Def -> Mid -> Str
                Sort by position up - Str -> Mid -> Def -> GK
                Sort by DOB up - Older players first
                Sort by DOB down - Younger players first

        Sorting the teams will only sort the team currently being
        edited as sorting all player for all teams in one go would 
        take too long. 

@Endnode
@Node "other" "PLAYERS OPTIONS"
@TOC "players"

        @{b}Transfer@{ub} - When a player is transferred click on this button
                   select the player and then his new team. The player
                   stays on both team lists to allow data such as goals
                   scored for the first team to still be used

        @{b}Delete@{ub} - This allows you to delete a player from the team list.
                 Don't do this if the player has scored goals or been
                 booked as this data will dissappear. You can use this
                 if a player is transferred without registering any goals,
                 etc and then adding him to the his new clubs team list
                 as a new player.

        @{b}Page@{ub} - This allow you to view the other players in a team. A
               shortcut for this is to press the RMB on the main window.

@Endnode
@Node "other2" "PLAYERS OPTIONS"
@TOC "players"

        @{b}Print@{ub} - Allows you to print out either the team currently 
               being edited, or all the teams. This output is sent to 
               RAM:, so after selecting print move the file to wherever
               you want. 

        @{b}Team@{ub} - This enables you to change the team currently being
               edited. The shortcut for this is to click on the top of
               the player window, left side to go backwards and right
               to go forwards

        @{b}Save@{ub} - Lets you save the information

@Endnode
@Node "calender" "CALENDER"
@TOC "insts"

        To be able to use Liga the fixtures for the league must be
        entered. This is where you do this. Select the home team first
        by clicking on the team name found on the right of the window
        and then the away team. For larger leagues the display only
        shows half the teams press the RMB on the list to view the
        others. Once you have entered the fixtures you can sort them
        into alphabetical order to make things look nice and finally
        save them.

@Endnode
@Node "Config1" "CONFIGURING LIGA PREFERENCES"
@TOC "insts"

        To make Liga correct for your league you must set up the
        preferences. This is done by selecting preferences from the 
        division menu, you now have the opportunity to change various
        aspect of your league

           @{b}Sorting Criteria@{ub} - This allows you select whether the
                league will be sorted by Goal Difference, Most wins 
                or Head to Head Meetings when teams have the same 
                number of points

           @{b}Points For Winner@{ub} - You can select whether there are 2 
                or 3 points for a win

           @{b}Favourite Team@{ub} - Select which team you support

           @{b}Cup Winner@{ub} - Select which team won the national cup

           @{b}Cup Loser@{ub} - Select which tean lost the national cup final
@Endnode
@Node "config2" " PREFERENCES PAGE TWO"
@TOC "insts"



           @{b}Promotion Zone@{ub} - This lets you set the number of teams 
                who are automatically promoted or qualify for the 
                Champions League

           @{b}UEFA Cup zone@{ub} - This lets you set the number of teams
                who qualify for the UEFA Cup or are in a promotion
                play-off position

           @{b}Relegation zone@{ub} - This lets you set the number of teams
                to be relegated
@Endnode
@Node "config3" "PREFERENCES PAGE THREE"
@TOC "insts"



           @{b}Match@{ub} - This allows the  match statistics, goalscorers,
                time, minute to be turned ON or OFF

           @{b}Team@{ub} - This enables the teams players/substitutes and 
                cards window to be turned ON or OFF

           @{b}Points Deducted@{ub} - If a team has had point deducted for 
                any reason then select the team and change the points
                from 0 to the required amount

       @{b}For users who only want to enter the results set Team and Match ON@{ub}
@Endnode
@Node "global" "GLOBAL PREFERENCES"
@TOC "insts"


        There are also three global preferences that can be set by
        selecting prefs from the project menu

           @{b}Auto-Load@{ub} - This enables Liga to open the league file
                currently loaded automatically, next time the program
                is started. This option can be set ON or OFF
 
           @{b}Auto-Table@{ub} - The league table is automatically displayed
                when the file is opened. This option can be set ON 
                or OFF

           @{b}Position Sign@{ub} - This allows you to set the sign for
                showing the positional changes of the teams. This
                option can be set to SIGN or NUMBER

@Endnode
@Node "import" "IMPORT"
@TOC "insts"

      Import :  Using this you can convert leagues made in :

                        Liga 345.
                        MUI_Ligamaster 
                        (many leagues as argentinen but only results)

@Endnode
@Node "fixt" "FIXTURES"
@TOC "insts"

        Once you have entered the fixture list using the calender
        option you can, when required, enter the results of matches.
        Clicking on the centre FIXTURE button will bring up a window
        containing the fixture list for the current week. Clicking 
        on either the << or >> button will change it to either the
        previous results or the next results. 

                        @{" Entering a Result " link "res"}

                        @{" Entering a Team   " link "play"}

@Endnode
@Node "res" "ENTERING A RESULT"
@TOC "insts"

To enter a result :

        1) Click once on the @{fg highlight}-:-@{fg shadow} between the two teams
        2) Type in the home teams score and press return
        3) Type in the away teams score and press return
        4) Click on the button MEMORY to store the result
        5) Click on the result just entered to display goalscorer
           information
        6) Enter the goal times in the left most column
        7) Set the order of goals scored by clicking on the second
           column.
        8) Click on the third column to select the goalscorer. If an
           Own goal is scored click on the team name to get the other
           teams player list
        9) The right most column lets you input the type of goal
           scored, The choices are Own Goal, Penalty, Free Kick or
           Headed Goal.
        10) Click on the memory button to store and close this window.
@Endnode
@Node "play" "RECORDING THE PLAYERS IN A TEAM"
@TOC "insts"

        Using this allows you to record the players in a team for that 
        match, as well as any substitutes. To add players click on a
        blank box and the player selection window will appear, select 
        the player and continue for the rest of the team.

        If there have been bookings or sending-offs in a match you 
        can record these by clicking on the small windows to the 
        right of the players name. The first one is for yellow cards 
        and the second for red cards. If a player is sent off for 
        two yellow cards click the yellow card box twice.

@Endnode
@Node "stand" "STANDINGS"
@TOC "insts"

        This enables you to display the table in a number of different
        ways by clicking on the relevant button

                HOME - Home Results Only
                AWAY - Away Results Only
                1st - First Half of the Season Results Only
                2nd - Second Half of the Season Results Only

        By clicking on the arrows you can set which round of fixtures
        the league table to be calculated should start and end on.
        This a nice way to see how team's form compare for a few
        games. Click on the button to the right of the arrows to
        display the table

        You can also print out the league table by clicking on the 
        PRINT button. At present the output is to file in RAM: not 
        to the printer directly. Once selected goto the RAM: drawer
        and move the file created to wherever you want. 
@Endnode
@Node "scorers" "SCORERS"
@TOC "insts"

        Clicking on this button allows you to see the goal scoring
        records of the players. You can view the players records for :

                        Total Goals
                        Own Goals
                        Penalties
                        Free Kicks
                        Headers
                        Goals Scored team-by-team

@Endnode
@Node "cards" "VIEWING CARD DETAILS

        This enables you to view the yellow and red cards that have 
        been issued. 

        Clicking on either button will show you the players who have 
        been booked or sent-off, together with how many times they 
        have offended.

        You can also view the dirtiest players by clicking on Dirt. 
        This works by giving a player receiving 3pts for every yellow 
        card and 5pts for every red, then adding up the total number 
        of points a player has amassed.

@Endnode
@Node "stats" "STATS"
@TOC "insts"

        This lets you monitor the league position graph of upto three
        different teams.

        You can also view 

           All goals scored in each round of matches
           The goals for home teams compared to away teams for each round
           The number of wins, draws and defeats in each round

@Endnode
@Node "matches" "MATCHES"
@TOC "insts"

        This option lets you view match results relating to the 
        selected criteria. These options are

                Biggest Win
                Biggest Draw
                Biggest Defeat
                Most goals in a game

        These options can be set for home fixtures, away fixtures 
        and all fixtures.

        You can also view a particular teams results in the same 
        way by selecting the team and then clicking on the required 
        button.


@Endnode
